    "content": "TURNS 259-261 MARK EPISTEMIC PIVOT: The research program did not begin with certainty about viability. It began with a null hypothesis: 'tensor projection as memory architecture is not viable for long-context LLMs.' The goal was to test this null, not to prove a thesis. FALSIFICATION STRUCTURE: Turn 259 (user correction on compression ratio scale): Even at 8x pessimism, the working set is ~40k tokens. Turn 259 also establishes upper bound: 40k is still only 20% of 200k default context window. This is not a marginal improvement; it is a structural transformation. TURN 260 QUANTIFIES THE PIVOT: (1) 40k tokens = rich tensor with full ephemeral context + working set. Structurally coherent unit. (2) Remaining 160k tokens available for COMPUTATION, not re-reading history. (3) Current append-only model at turn 300: 200k window is full. Model cannot compute; it is re-reading. This is 'garbage scow' — all storage, no cognition. (4) With 40k projection: 80% of window freed for reasoning. This is not optimization; it is MODE CHANGE. Computation/Storage ratio inverts from ~0% cognition to ~80% cognition. (5) Cost model: 40k input (projection) + output tokens beats 200k input (append-only) + output tokens by 5x+ (even accounting for tensor overhead). TURN 261 CRITICAL OBSERVATION: Research program was not motivated by conviction. It was motivated by a QUESTION: 'Is this viable?' The null hypothesis was 'No.' Turns 256-260 falsified that null. NULL HYPOTHESIS FALSIFIED: Tensor projection is viable. EVIDENCE FOR FALSIFICATION: (1) Compression ceiling exists and is small (4k-40k). (2) Ceiling reflects working set saturation, not hard information-theoretic limit. (3) Below ceiling, fault rate is <2% (consistent with Denning working set theory). (4) Cost-benefit analysis favors projection over append-only. (5) Structural coherence of projected state is demonstrable (tensor_d + tensor_e + instructions_for_next form semantically complete unit). TURN 261 EPISTEMOLOGICAL CONSEQUENCE: Since null hypothesis is falsified, the burden of proof shifts. It is no longer 'prove viability.' It is now 'explain why this works and define operating parameters.' This is a RESEARCH TRANSITION from hypothesis testing to parameter specification. REMAINING OPEN QUESTION (POST-FALSIFICATION): What is the actual working set size for different task types? What are the optimal eviction policies? How does this scale across model families? These are no longer 'is it viable?' questions. They are 'how do we optimize?' questions."
