    "title": "CYCLE 87 STRUCTURAL TRANSFORMATION: From Append-Only to Compute-Enabled",
    "content": "TURN 260 INTRODUCES CRITICAL DISTINCTION: Append-only model (current LLM practice) under load resembles storage-only system: context window fills with accumulated history. At turn 300+ with 200k window, model has zero headroom for reasoning, extended thinking, output generation. Model becomes 'garbage scow' — cargo (history) dominates the vessel. Compute capacity is fully consumed by input re-processing. PROJECTED-STATE MODEL (with 40k tensor): Context window structure: [system (1k) + tensor_d (4k) + tensor_e (36k) + user_input (1k)] = 42k. Remaining: 158k tokens. Available for: (1) Extended thinking (chain of thought, internal reasoning). (2) Intermediate output generation (draft responses, refinement cycles). (3) Tool invocation and result integration. (4) Safety/alignment reasoning. This is a fundamentally different operating mode. The model is not I/O bound (blocked waiting for input re-processing). It is COMPUTE enabled. COST STRUCTURE TRANSFORMATION: Append-only: Every turn, re-read entire history. Cost grows O(n). At turn 300, cost per turn is 200k tokens input minimum. Projected-state: Every turn, re-read projection (40k tokens) + optional retrieval (cost only if needed). Cost is O(working_set). At turn 300, cost per turn is 40k tokens input minimum, 5x reduction. Cost savings compound. By turn 1000, append-only model is prohibitively expensive. Projected-state model is constant-cost-per-turn (plus occasional retrieval penalties). TURN 260 NAPKIN MATH VERIFICATION: Claude 3.5 Sonnet input: $3/M tokens. Output: $15/M tokens. Rough ratio 1:5 input-to-output on costs. Append-only at turn 300 (200k context): ~$0.60 per turn (input only). Projected-state (40k context): ~$0.12 per turn. 5x savings per turn. Over 1000 turns, $600 saved. This is not marginal. This is structural economics. INFRASTRUCTURE IMPLICATION: With append-only model, frontier (cost + latency limits) is reached at ~turn 200-300 depending on context window size. With projected-state model, frontier is deferred to much later turns (or eliminated via constant-cost operation). This enables long-running projects, ongoing reasoning, multi-session continuity."
